{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddceee2df-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s2285a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2285a"},"text":"§ 2285a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Acquisition of obligations involving loan guarantees for New York City","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in any provision of law shall be construed to authorize the Federal Financing Bank to acquire any obligation the payment of interest or principal of which has at any time been guaranteed in whole or in part under title I of the New York City Loan Guarantee Act of 1978.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddceee2e0-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/339/tII/s201/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–339, title II, § 201(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/467"},"text":"92 Stat. 467","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddceee2e1-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddceee2e2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddceee2e3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Title I of the New York City Loan Guarantee Act of 1978, referred to in text, is title I of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/339"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–339","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/460"},"text":"92 Stat. 460","children":[],"tail":", which was classified generally to subchapter II (§ 1521 et seq.) of chapter 27 of former Title 31, and was omitted from the Code in the general revision and reenactment of Title 31, Money and Finance, by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/877"},"text":"96 Stat. 877","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddceee2e4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the New York City Loan Guarantee Act of 1978, and not as part of the Federal Financing Bank Act of 1973 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
